Officers made the grim discovery during a patrol through the streets of the township on Thursday morning. JOHANNESBURG - Police have discovered the decapitated body of a two-month-old in Thokoza, south of Johannesburg. Officers made the grim discovery during a patrol through the streets of the township on Thursday morning. The circumstances around the crime have not yet been established.The police s Lesetja Mathobela says, The body was found on Thursday near a hostel in Thokoza and it looks like the baby is about two-months-old. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)